If you talk to an older doctor who's been practicing for many decades he'll tell you back in the day Alzheimer's and dementia were so rare that if there was a patient with Alzheimer's in the hospital they called all the medical students to go see him because it was such a rarity.

Any old doctor will confirm that the number of patients with dementia has simply exploded in recent decades. This is still living memory, but once that generation of old doctors passes, they are 100% going to lie about it and make up some fake numbers to show there was no change.
